ut next week lmao. Pre order/pre save nowpic.twitter.com/ZjO6pXx2ZG|date=2020-03-18|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> The song was made available for [[pre-order]] on the same day.<ref name=\"ein2\"/>\n\n=== \"Poppin challenge\" ===\nOn 30 March 2020, KSI announced via social media that he would be hosting a competition called \"#PoppinChallenge\". He asked people to record and submit their own verses for \"Poppin\", and the best verse, decided by public vote, will replace Lil Pump's verse on a remix of the song which will appear on the deluxe edition of KSI's upcoming 2020 album ''Dissimulation''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/KSIOlajidebt/status/1244735326179950593|title=Got a big one for you  #poppinchallengepic.twitter.com/NWe2Lq74Gq|last=KSI|date=2020-03-30|website=@KSIOlajidebt|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> On 17 April 2020, American YouTube rapper Crypt was announced as the winner of the competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oMIRi2eTgb0|title=The Winner Of The Poppin Challenge Is...|last=|first=|date=17 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QOCY2QC7AWY|title=I WON THE KSI POPPIN' CHALLENGE|last=|first=|date=17 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song entered the UK Singles Chart at number 43.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48106/ksi/|title=KSI {{!}} full Official Chart History {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> It dropped to number 56 the following week, before dropping out of the top 100.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Music video ==\nAn audio visualiser video for the song was uploaded to KSI's [[YouTube]] channel on 26 March 2020. As of April 2020, it has 6 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GGLE8gk9fng|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp)|date=26 March 2020|via=[[YouTube]]|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref> The music video, directed by TajvsJaj, was filmed in [[Los Angeles]] in March 2020 and was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 3 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://grmdaily.com/video/ksi-poppin-lil-pump-smokepurpp|title=KSI Gives Visual Treatment To \"Poppin\" Featuring Lil Pump & Smokepurpp|last=|first=|date=3 April 2020|website=[[GRM Daily]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> The music video stars Asian dancer Bailey Sok and features cameo appearances from American actor and comedian [[King Bach]] and two of the song's producers, Diego Ave and Mally Mall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://grungecake.com/ksi-popping-lil-pump-smokepurpp/articles/65556|title=English rapper KSI enlists Lil Pump and Smokepurpp for 'Poppin': Watch|date=2020-04-06|website=GRUNGECAKE|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> As of April 2020, it has 7 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xa0qshcRhDQ|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) [Official Music Video]|last=|first=|date=3 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref> A [[Making-of|behind-the-scenes]] video of the filming of the music video was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 10 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fmf_KsHjGC8|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) [Behind The Scenes]|last=|first=|date=10 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| title1 = Poppin\n| note1 = featuring [[Lil Pump]] and [[Smokepurpp]]\n| length1 = 3:33\n| length6 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| l